<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 5:02PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Clarke, southeastern
Jackson, northwestern Wilkes, Oglethorpe and Madison Counties through
530 PM EDT...
At 502 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Colbert, or near
Danielsville, moving south at 30 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Commerce, Danielsville, Lexington, Athens, Arcade,
Nicholson, Comer, Winterville, Crawford, Colbert, Arnoldsville, Ila,
Carlton, Hull, Athens-Clarke County, Westgate Park, Delhi, Diamond
Hill and Smithonia.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
